Install node from http://nodejs.org

 *** inside project root ***

To install all project dependencies:
- npm run build

To clean project dependencies:
- npm run clean

To run tests:
- if you are running the tests using an IDE make sure to add the "--no-timeouts --recursive" arguments
- npm run test

Guide:
https://blog.testproject.io/2018/03/08/selenium-javascript-best-practices/
https://nehalist.io/selenium-tests-with-mocha-and-chai-in-javascript/
https://jaketrent.com/post/run-single-mocha-test/

Helpful tool for getting elements xpaths:
- XPath Generator - chrome extension

To run a single describe function:
- add ".only()" to the function call i.e. describe.only(() => { ... });
- this can also be done to test cases i.e. it.only(() => { ... });

For expect tests:
    chai

For syntax information:
    selenium
    mocha
    javascript

